The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Whatmore seeks time

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Dav Whatmore still hasnt responded to a Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) communication, but has promised to get back to them after Thursdays match against the West Indies. 

The Telegraph had reported on Wednesday that there was no response from the Bangladesh coach to the BCB asking whether he would at least be willing to stay on till the end of the home series versus India (May 29). Whatmores contract is till April 29. 

It is understood that the BCB has formed a six-member committee, led by its vice-president Shahnarul Kabir Shahen, to look into the matter at its Executive Board meeting on Wednesday. 

The committee is expected to arrive at a decision by the end of this month. 




